"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1968510-Usain-Bolt-Olympic-Games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  The fastest man in history, Usain Bolt, has confessed he decided against going to the Paris 2024 Olympics due to injury concerns making him feel \\\"weird\\\" about being seen on crutches.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 30, \"end\": 40, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Usain Bolt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite his legendary status with eight Olympic golds and still holding three world records, Bolt had to withdraw his plans of attending this year's Games as a spectator.\", \"from\": 186, \"to\": 356, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He suffered a nasty fall during a charity football match organised by Unicef on June 9, which led to a significant Achilles tendon injury.\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 427, \"end\": 433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Unicef\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\"}, {\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"score\": 0.9999998930984532, \"rank\": 1.0690136060807026e-07, \"text\": \"Achilles\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opening up about his choice to skip the event on the \\\"High Performance\\\" podcast, Bolt explained the rationale behind his decision: \\\"I was supposed to go with my family, but I injured myself,\\\" and further clarified, \\\"I was playing a charity game, a football match, for soccer for Unicef and I ruptured my Achilles.\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 776, \"end\": 782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Unicef\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\"}, {\"begin\": 801, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"score\": 0.9999998930984532, \"rank\": 1.0690136060807026e-07, \"text\": \"Achilles\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not want to go on crutches.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's my first time going without and not competing, so it would look weird for every time you see me on TV I am on crutches like this.\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I was just like, you know what, let me just stay home.\\\"\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bolt shared that although he's retired from competition, the sting of missing the Games lingers, especially since he sat out of the crowdless Tokyo Olympics too, an event he had participated in since his Olympic debut in Athens in 2004, remarking how challenging he found being merely a spectator.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9911917596383544, \"rank\": 0.008886500860484378, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Jamaican sprinting icon expressed a profound sense of longing for the track, recounting to AFP: \\\"I really missed it.\", 